05480nam a22008775i 9780823298389DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20212021nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808232983897 a10.1515/97808232983892doi  a(DE-B1597)612810  a(OCoLC)1291506848  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 4aJA71b.M65913 2021 7aLIT0041002bisacsh04a320.01/12231 aMoreiras, Alberto, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aInfrapolitics :bA Handbook /cAlberto Moreiras. 1aNew York, NY : bFordham University Press, c[2021] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (272 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface to the English- Language Edition -- tExergue. On Jacques Derrida’s Glas: A Possible Second Moment in Deconstruction -- t1. The Last God: María Zambrano’s Life without Texture -- t2. The Wolf’s Hide: Ontotheological Militancies -- t3. Infrapolitical Distance: A Second Note on the Concept of Distance in Felipe Martínez Marzoa -- t4. Infrapolitics and the Politics of Infrapolitics -- t5. The Absolute Difference between Life and Politics -- t6. A Politics of Separation: An Alternative Politicity -- t7. Infrapolitical Derrida: The Ontic Determination of Politics beyond Empiricism -- t8. A Negation of the Anarchy Principle -- t9. On the Illegal Condition in the State of Extraction: How Not to Be an Informant -- tNotes -- tWorks Cited -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe personal is not political, even if politics marks it and, in many cases, determines it. Infrapolitics seeks to understand conditions of existence that are not reducible to political life and that exceed any definition of world bound to political determinations. It seeks to mobilize an exteriority without which politics could only be business or administration, that is, oppression. It demands a change in seeing and an everyday practice that subtracts from political totalization in the name of a new production of desire, of a new emancipation, and of a conception of experience that can breach the general captivation of life.In this book, Alberto Moreiras describes a form of thought aiming to provide content for a form of life and to offer a new theoretical practice for concrete existence. The book provides a genealogy of the notion of infrapolitics and places it within contemporary philosophical reflection, examining its deployment in the wake of postphenomenology and deconstruction, Lacanian analysis, the principle of anarchy, and an egalitarian symbolization of social life. In doing so, Moreiras elaborates Infrapolitics as both a general critique of the political apparatus and as an imperative horizon for existential self-understanding.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 0aSociologyxPhilosophy. 4aLatin American Studies. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh  aAnarchy.  aDeconstruction.  aDemocracy.  aExistence.  aImpolitical.  aInfrapolitics.  aOntotheology.  aPosthegemony.  aTrue Life.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073909140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823298